</div>
<h3 id=3D"APIDesignStandards-DELETE">DELETE</h3>
<p>DELETE is used to completely remove a resource instance. This is a safe =
operation in that a call can be made multiple times and only the targeted r=
esource should be deleted, however note that a second call should be an err=
or (resource not found) if the DELETE has been completed.</p>
<p><strong>Note</strong>. A request body cannot be sent when using the DELE=
TE verb.</p>
<p><strong>Examples:</strong></p>
<p>DELETE /customers/12345</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">DELETE request: single resource</b><span class=3D"c=
ollapse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expan=
d-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expan=
d source</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Confluence; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Confl=
uence">DELETE /customers/12345 HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">DELETE response: single resource</b><span class=3D"=
collapse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expa=
nd-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expa=
nd source</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Confluence; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Confl=
uence">HTTP/1.1 204 No Content
Content-Type: application/json</pre>
</div>
</div>
