<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Confluence; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Confl=
uence">HTTP/1.1 204 No Content
Content-Type: application/json</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"APIDesignStandards-PATCH">PATCH</h3>
<p>PATCH is used to update a subset of attributes for a resource. This is a=
n unsafe operation in that the state of a resource may be different after a=
pplying the same PATCH request multiple times due to simultaneous updates a=
pplied by other parties. There are various PATCH request formats in use wit=
hin the industry. Westpac Mesh has adopted the&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://tool=
s.ietf.org/html/rfc7396" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">JSON Merg=
e PATCH</a>&nbsp;format as it supports the same request format as used for =
POST and PUT verbs.</p>
<p><strong>Note</strong>. The target resource URI may identify a single obj=
ect or a collection of objects.&nbsp; If it identifies a collection of obje=
cts only existing objects within the collection can be updated - you cannot=
 insert or delete objects within the collection using PATCH.</p>
<p><strong>Examples:</strong></p>
<p>PATCH /customers/12345</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">PATCH request: single resource</b><span class=3D"co=
llapse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand=
-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand=
 source</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Confluence; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Confl=
uence">PATCH /customers/12345 HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/merge-patch+json
=20
{
   "lastName": "Johnson",
   "middleName": null
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">PATCH response: single resource</b><span class=3D"c=
ollapse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expan=
d-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expan=
d source</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Confluence; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Confl=
uence">HTTP/1.1 204 No Content
Content-Type: application/json</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p>PATCH /customers&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">PATCH request: collection resource</b><span class=
=3D"collapse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"=
expand-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">=
Expand source</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Confluence; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Confl=
uence">PATCH /customers HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/merge-patch+json
=20
[
   {
      "customerId": {
         "id": "1234",
         "idScheme": "CustomerInternalId"
      },
      "lastName": "Johnson",
      "middleName": null
   },
   {
      "customerId": {
         "id": "5678",
         "idScheme": "CustomerInternalId"
      },
      "lastName": "Warren",
      "firstName": "Jennifer"
   }
]</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">PATCH response: collection resource</b><span class=
=3D"collapse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"=
expand-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">=
Expand source</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Confluence; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Confl=
uence">HTTP/1.1 204 No Content
Content-Type: application/json</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"APIDesignStandards-HEAD">HEAD</h3>
<p>HEAD is to be used for safe to repeat queries. The use of HEAD must not =
lead to a change of resource state, but it is valid for resource state to c=
hange between queries due to other impacting factors. Note that as HEAD is =
used for probing API availability, response payload size, and cache expiry,=
 the actual resource will NOT be returned.</p>
<p><strong>Examples:</strong></p>
<p>HEAD /customers/12345</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">HEAD request</b><span class=3D"collapse-source expa=
nd-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-control-icon icon=
">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand source</span></sp=
an><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Confluence; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Confl=
uence">GET /customers/12345 HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">HEAD response</b><span class=3D"collapse-source exp=
and-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-control-icon ico=
n">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand source</span></s=
pan><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Confluence; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Confl=
uence">HTTP/1.1 200 Ok
Content-Type: application/json
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"APIDesignStandards-page_sort_filterPaging,SortingandFiltering"><s=
pan class=3D"confluence-anchor-link" id=3D"APIDesignStandards-page_sort_fil=
ter"></span>Paging, Sorting and Filtering</h2>
<p>Please refer to <a href=3D"/display/MESH/Pattern+9%3A+Paging%2C+Sorting+=
and+Filtering">Pattern 9: Paging, Sorting and Filtering</a></p>
<h2 id=3D"APIDesignStandards-response_codesResponseStatusCodes"><span class=
=3D"confluence-anchor-link" id=3D"APIDesignStandards-response_codes"></span=
>Response Status Codes</h2>
<h3 id=3D"APIDesignStandards-Summary.2">Summary</h3>
<p>Most HTTP common response codes are generally well understood by API con=
sumers, such as 404 =E2=80=93 Not Found. However, others are less commonly =
understood, and it is important designers and implementers are consistent i=
n how they are used in order to breed a consistent familiarity for API cons=
umers. A good accessible resource for HTTP codes and their meanings is in W=
ikipedia:&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_HTTP_status=
_codes" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/List_of_HTTP_status_codes</a></p>
<p class=3D"TableHeading">A summary table is provided below showing which c=
odes are in use on Westpac Mesh. If the code is not in this table, it is no=
t to be used as a response code. If a use case is not covered and requires =
a new response code, then propose through program architecture. Note that o=
nly a few combinations are invalid due to the filtering down of response st=
atus codes.</p>
